dcterms:description: The Procgen benchmark suite consists of 16 video games that procedurally generate distinct levels for each game, allowing for virtually unlimited levels. It is designed to evaluate zero-shot generalization in reinforcement learning.
dcterms:title: Procgen benchmark suite

dcterms:description: The Atari dataset is used for unsupervised state representation learning, providing a variety of games to evaluate learning algorithms.
dcterms:title: Atari

dcterms:description: The Ising model is used as a toy example to illustrate concepts in reinforcement learning, particularly in the context of behavioral similarity and representation learning.
dcterms:title: Ising model (used as a toy example)
